<item>
            <title>[DERBY-4967] Handle interrupt received while waiting for database lock</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-4967</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Subtask of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-4741&quot; title=&quot;Make embedded Derby work reliably in the presence of thread interrupts&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-4741&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-4741&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: this issue tracks the changes needed to handle interrupt received while a thread is waiting for a database lock.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12495293">DERBY-4967</key>
            <summary>Handle interrupt received while waiting for database lock</summary>
